node.text:
Are you all worried about your placement preparations?😟
Well, here we are with our placement series emphasizing on virtual placements faced by our LCC team who got an opportunity to be placed in great companies in the batch of 2021.🤓
They are eager to provide you with a detailed insight into various stages in the campus placement process and will be sharing tips to successfully clear all the stages.

 All of your queries will be answered by them!🎊
Also Dr. Pradeep Manjunath, training and placement officer, JSSSTU, will be addressing you in our 1st episode 🎙️

Let's dive into and make the most of it!

Follow us on our Instagram page @linuxcampusclub for more updates!

LCC JSSSTU, Department of Computer Science and Engineering presents 🐧

🎉🎉 FOSS CAMP 2021-22 🎉🎉
 26th December - 2nd January
Hey folks, 📢

LCC JSSSTU is here with FOSS CAMP, our annual technical fest 🎉! FOSS CAMP consists of a curated collection of technical and non-technical events, with the goal of tickling both sides of your brain 🧠. Here's a little teaser of the events we have in store for you 👀

Code Con 👨🏻‍💻👩🏻‍💻
Spider Web 🕷️🕸️
DeCrypto 🔑
Bermuda Triangle 🔺
Trackback 🔙

And last, but certainly not least, the star ⭐ of FOSS CAMP, Vivechan, aimed at providing students with a complete interview experience via a mock placement event! 💼

Excited? Looking to sign up? Join our discord server and follow our instagram page to stay tuned for further details regarding each event! 😉

Discord : https://bit.ly/lcc-sjce-discord

For further queries
Contact :
Narayan - 9483717117 ( @narayanbhat166 )

Greetings from LCC-SJCE🐧

Missed us? Don't worry, we are back with a follow up event  for Let's React ✨

React is only half the piece of a puzzle 🧩 that is Full-Stack Development. You learnt 🧠 how to render the data beautifully to the user, but now the question 🤔 is, where does this data come from? To answer this question, we are here with GET, set, POST ! 

In this event, we will be covering the basics 👶 of backend development. Continuing on with the E-commerce example, we will help you get started on your journey of building full stack applications!

Hope to see you all there!

node.text:
Hey everyone!🌟✨
Greetings from LCC-SJCE🐧

We are here  with another amazing session for you 🥁  Let's React ✨
We plan to take you from a very basic understanding 👶🏻 of Reactjs to a self sufficient one🕵🏻‍♀🕵🏻 .

React is a free and open-source front-end JavaScript library for building user interfaces or UI components. It is one of the most widely used tools in the industry. 👩🏻‍💻👨🏻‍💻. We will help you uncover the mystery of React, its flexibility and usefulness by building an e-commerce page in react.

Time, tide and Javascript waits for none just like how we can't wait to see you guys for our first in-person event!🙌🏻

Registration link in the bio! (3rd years only)

🗓 Date : 23rd and 24th October
🕰 Time : 3:00pm to 5:00pm and 10:00am to 12:00pm
🗺 Venue : Cs Department

Contact 📞:
9483717117 - Narayan
7619391823 - Sparsh

Hello everyone! 🐧🐧
Hope you all are doing well. We are proud to announce that we have conducted our second event, Projectify (building a project). ✨💫

It was a week long event. Projects are a crucial part for building an impressive resume and we are thankful to our seniors for their guidance while building our projects, and this event was conducted to carry on that tradition. 36 students were shortlisted, and they were divided into teams of 4-5. Mentors were assigned, who guided them to build a project. The projects were across 3 verticals - web development, mobile app development and machine learning. 🤯🧠

The participants successfully completed the projects and even hosted it on Heroku. We chose one team in each domain as outstanding performer. 
We really enjoyed conducting it! 😁😁
